dcterms:description: A light and sweet crude oil that is ideal for gasoline refining, extracted from land wells in the United States and transported to Cushing, Oklahoma. It serves as the main benchmark for oil used within the United States.
dcterms:title: WTI (West Texas Intermediate) Crude Oil Daily Spot Price

dcterms:description: A blend of oil from four fields in the North Sea, Brent is the most popular oil contracted globally, making up approximately two-thirds of all global crude contracts. It is light and sweet, distilled into high-value products.
dcterms:title: Brent Crude Oil Daily Spot Price

dcterms:description: Also known as Fateh, Dubai Crude is a medium density crude oil with higher sulfur content than WTI and Brent. It is used as a pricing benchmark for crude oil exports from the Persian Gulf to Asian-Pacific markets.
dcterms:title: Dubai Crude Oil Monthly Average Price
